I am a professional in the FPGA industry.
And in Vivado, it is legal to assign logic variables through both blocking and non blocking methods, as shown in the following code.

                  module test(
                      input clk,
                      input [1:0] a,
                      output logic [1:0] b
                      );
                  assign b[0] = a[0];
                  always_ff @ (posedge clk)
                      b[1] <= a[1];
                  endmodule

I don't know if this approach is legal in IC design, so I can't be sure if it's a bug or a feature.
Any response will be appreciated.
